BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:botOWrlpqs4d1S846nXBu
SUMMARY:Living with Conviction: Sentenced to Debt for Life in Washington St
	ate Exhibit
DTSTAMP:20260413T050911Z
DTSTART:20260419T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sunday\, April 19\, 2026\, 10am - 6pm\n\nThis exhibitconfronts 
	how Washington courts have been sentencing people not only to prison but a
	lso to a lifetime of debt.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Lo
	cation: Level 8 - Gallery\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not re
	quired.\n\nDetailed Description: "Living with Conviction: Sentenced to Deb
	t for Life in Washington State" confronts how Washington courts have been 
	sentencing people not only to prison but also to a lifetime of debt. The p
	roject leverages multimedia storytelling and community conversations to ra
	ise awareness about and advocate for an end to crippling court-imposed cos
	ts\, fees\, fines\, and restitution\, commonly referred to as Legal Financ
	ial Obligations\, or LFOs. "Living with Conviction: Sentenced to Debt for 
	Life in Washington State\," goes beyond polarizing headlines and statistic
	s\, shining a light on this injustice by sharing stories of our common hum
	anity.\, Thanks to our partner\n\nLiving with Conviction .\, Thanks to our
	 sponsor\n\nThe Seattle Public Library Foundation .\n\nEvent Logistics: Th
	e gallery is open during Central Libray's open hours.\, Living with Convic
	tion is a 501\\(c\\)\\(3\\) nonprofit that works to secure economic and ra
	cial justice with and by marginalized communities\, especially formerly in
	carcerated\, through community-driven research\, storytelling\, and legal 
	empowerment strategies.\, This exhibit runs through July 26\, 2026\, Learn
	 more about\n\nExhibits .\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this 
	event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can p
	rovide accommodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Plea
	se\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accom
	modations.\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\n\nhttp
	s://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/living-with-conviction-sentenced
	-to-debt-for-life-in-washington-state-exhibit/18572479/2026-04-19T00\n\nFr
	om SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/living-with-conviction-se
	ntenced-to-debt-for-life-in-washington-state-exhibit/18572479/2026-04-19T0
	0
LOCATION:Northwest Worklofts (Commons)\, 107 West Denny Way\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
