UID:li05VAsLzZS7EH0plcH8Z
SUMMARY:Earth Day at Seattle: Kubota Garden
DTSTAMP:20260413T050911Z
DTSTART:20260422T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Kubota Gardens Natural 
	Area. \\nCelebrate Earth Day with EarthCorps and Seattle Parks by restorin
	g a beloved park! Located in the Rainier Beach Neighborhood in SE Seattle\
	\\, Kubota Garden is an American-Japanese Garden designed and built by Mr.
	 Fujitaro Kubota. Construction of this gem began in 1927 and lasted beyond
	 the lifetime of Mr. Kubota. Today\\\, the Gardens are owned by the City o
	f Seattle and maintained by the Seattle Parks Department. The garden is su
	rrounded by a natural buffer of urban forest\\\, some of which has only re
	cently been acquired by the city. \\nDuring this event\\\, we’ll be planti
	ng native trees\\\, shrubs\\\, and ground cover! Water\\\, tea\\\, snacks\
	\\, and tools will be provided. \\nRegister to meet.\n\nhttps://www.seattl
	eparksfoundation.org/event/earth-day-at-seattle-kubota-garden/\n\nFrom The
	 Seattle Parks Foundation
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/earth-day-at-seattle-kubot
	a-garden/
LOCATION:WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-parks-foundation
CATEGORIES:The Seattle Parks Foundation
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
